  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nfoundry 4.7.0 (forge 0.2.0)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nCurrently when I try to import a specific .sol file from a remote address I get errors:\r\n\r\n```\r\n//SPDX-License-Identifier: Unlicense\r\npragma solidity >=0.8.13;\r\n\r\nimport \"https://gist.githubusercontent.com/JofArnold/bf2c4a094fcdd4aee2f52983c7714de8/raw/f8ca925324b3bf53354c84d47d080e6a87439233/BoredApeYachtClub.sol\";\r\n\r\n// TODO: Implement all user stories and one of the feature request\r\ncontract Game {\r\n    uint256 public x;\r\n\r\n    constructor() {\r\n        x = 4;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nCompiler run failed:\r\nError (6275): Source \"https://gist.githubusercontent.com/JofArnold/bf2c4a094fcdd4aee2f52983c7714de8/raw/f8ca925324b3bf53354c84d47d080e6a87439233/BoredApeYachtClub.sol\" not found: File not found. Searched the following locations: \"/home/ubuntu/solidity-exercise\".\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt treats the remote address like a local import.\r\n\r\nSame code works in Remix, as well as with Hardhat/Truffle.\r\n\r\nI may be mistaken, please let me know if there's any workaround for this.",
